summary: Okay I'm like 84028482947236282% hyped for Endgame and I keep thinking about what we may or may not see and because it's the MCU...
body:
Okay I’m like 84028482947236282% hyped for Endgame and I keep thinking about what we may or may not see and because it’s the MCU I just keep thinking about OMG WHAT COULD THE CREDIT SCENES BE. And this happened and now I need it.

So picture we get this homage to the first Avengers - the shawarma scene. Everyone is at Avengers HQ, they’re having a party/bbq/whatever. Just hanging out drinking and conversing like a normal group of friends. And it’s like everyone. Even Clint’s family is there and everyone is just happy and laughing and there.

Carol is talking to Sam, Bucky, and Nat when Steve walks up and says, “Sorry to interrupt. I’ve got something I wanted to give you.” In his hands is his notebook from TWS, the one of things to catch up on.

Carol looks confused, does her little head tilt squint thing that’s so adorable and is like “What’s this?” and starts flipping through it.

Nat and Sam share a LOOK because they know what it is.

He claps his hand on her back/shoulder and is like “Trust me. You’re gonna need some of it,” and there’s this pause, where he gets his super fond big brother Captain America look as he looks at her, “Captain.”

And like… obviously Steve knows she has knowledge of A LOT in there because she wasn’t gone as long as he was but it’s Steve being so Steve. The notebook is more a symbol than anything, acknowledging that sorta shared history and passing the torch all at once, and my stupid brain can’t stop thinking about this happening and I want to die.

MARVEL TEAM-UP #4

CLINT MCELROY (W)

Ig Guara (A)

Cover by ANNA RUD

VARIANT COVER BY  TODD NAUCK

A BRAND-NEW STORY BEGINS HERE!

• The sudden reappearance of Mar-Vell, the first Captain Marvel, draws Carol Danvers and Kamala Khan back together for an out-of-this-world adventure!

• But is the man behind the mask who he claims to be? And can Ms. Marvel and Captain Marvel stay on the same page long enough to find out?

• Podcast superstar and Adventure Zone scribe CLINT McELROY and ALL-NEW WOLVERINE artist Ig Guara, take the reins of an electrifying new team-up tale!

32 PGS./Rated T+ …$3.99
